        "subject": "LU-18569 tests: skip ls for ubuntu clients on sanity-sec/75a",
        "message": "LU-18569 tests: skip ls for ubuntu clients on sanity-sec/75a\n\nThere seem to be an unusual number of network timeouts when running\n\"ls -l\" in sanity-sec/75a on Ubuntu clients only. This patch skips\n\"ls\" on Ubuntu clients to investigate whether the frequency of\nfailures will be reduced on the test system for this test.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: testlist=sanity-sec env=ONLY=75a,ONLY_REPEAT=100 clientdistro=ubuntu2404\nSigned-off-by: Marc Vef <mvef@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ie7c189101dc4c2743991f9d1adcf5bd2675cc7be\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61583\nReviewed-by: Sebastien Buisson <sbuisson@ddn.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@dilger.ca>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
